{"id":612,"date":"2017-03-11T08:34:24","date_gmt":"2017-03-11T08:34:24","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=612"},"modified":"2020-10-22T20:12:30","modified_gmt":"2020-10-22T20:12:30","slug":"tcpdf-error-image-unable-to-get-the-size-of-the-image","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/tcpdf-error-image-unable-to-get-the-size-of-the-image\/","title":{"rendered":"TCPDF ERROR: [Image] Unable to Get the Size of the Image"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><strong>Unable to get the size of the image<\/strong> is an error thrown if <strong>TCPDF<\/strong> can&#8217;t fetch the image when using an absolute path.<\/p>\n<p>The problem starts showing after you add a custom absolute URL in <strong>Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;PDF<\/strong>, in this case, the TCPDF is trying to fetch the image with a cURL request but the request is unsuccessful, you can contact your hosting provider to make sure that your cURL extension is properly configured and it&#8217;s up to date, otherwise try to follow the steps below and add the relative path to your logo image.<\/p>\n<p>Before start, the workaround for this problem makes sure that the URL you have added in <strong>Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;PDF<\/strong> for the custom pdf logo image is valid and the image exists if the problem still exists try to add a relative path like mentioned below.<\/p>\n<p>Upload the image to the<strong> folder where Perfex CRM is installed<\/strong> for example <strong>mylogo.jpg<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Go to Setup -&gt; Settings -&gt; PDF -&gt; <strong>Custom PDF Company Logo URL<\/strong> and <strong>only<\/strong> add mylogo<strong>.jpg<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-613\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/custom-pdf-logo-image.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"825\" height=\"88\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/custom-pdf-logo-image.png 825w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/custom-pdf-logo-image-300x32.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/custom-pdf-logo-image-768x82.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/custom-pdf-logo-image-60x6.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/custom-pdf-logo-image-150x16.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px\" \/><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>In this case, the relative path (crm_installation_path\/mylogo.jpg) for the image will be used and the script will be able to fetch the image.<\/p>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-info \">The logo image must be in the folder where Perfex CRM is installed.<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Unable to get the size of the image is an error thrown if TCPDF can&#8217;t fetch the image when using an absolute path. The problem starts showing after you add a custom absolute URL in Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;PDF, in this case, the TCPDF is trying to fetch the image with a cURL request but the request is [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[36],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-612","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-common-issues"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/612","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=612"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/612\/revisions"}],"wp